     "source": "An infographic framework of GeoAI ethics based on news data.pdf",
     "content": "acquisition speed and analytical responsiveness  played a more critical role. Preprocessing Nonexistence Integration Nonexistence Storage and management Nonexistence Analysis and processing Existence Application and  dissemination Nonexistence AI-driven  attributes Untimely maintenance of  training data Existence The case involved multiple incidents occurring in real-world traffic, during which Cruise  maintained that its automated systems were not at fault. However, these incidents took  place in complex and evolving urban environments, where human behaviors such as  distracted driving and illegal overtaking are increasingly common. If training datasets  are not routinely updated to reflect such behavioral shifts, autonomous systems may  struggle to anticipate or respond appropriately. Additionally, the case provided little  detail on how the underlying models made decisions in each scenario. The absence of  transparency and reproducibility in the system’s decision-making process complicates  efforts to evaluate the appropriateness of its responses. Taken together, these factors  suggest potential gaps between the system’s training context and actual deployment  conditions, raising ongoing concerns among the public and regulators.  Opacity or weak  reproducibility Existence Limitations of traditional  supervision methods Nonexistence 198  C. CHEN ET AL. requiring urgent remediation. These data highlight  vulnerable groups’ persistent challenges and under - score the need for targeted interventions and policy  reforms to uphold equal rights and promote inclu - sive societies. 4.2. Impact attributes As shown in Figure 13 , of the cases with a defined  scope, 40.37% are global (abbreviated as “glo” in  the figure), 42.49% are individual (abbreviated as  “ind” in the figure), and 17.14% are local (abbre - viated as “loc” in the figure). This distribution  suggests a nuanced manifestation of phenomena at  different scales, potentially indicating different  impacts,"
