     "content": "Shapley value-  based  explanations Incurring game theory-  based  shapley values to determine  contribution of each input  feature towards a given result SHAP Li (2022), Yang  et al. (2021), Simini  et al. (2021), Wang,  Wang, et al. ( 2021) Gradient- based  explanations Measuring changes from the  reference towards the input  along a path, for example,  comparing layer to layer or  neuron to layer Integrated gradient Luo et al. (2021) Layer- based  explanations Attributing each neuron layer  calculated from their  relevance, which measures  their contribution towards the  generated results Layer- wise  relevance  propagation  (LRP) Sonnewald and  Lguensat  (2021) Local surrogate  models Replacing decision function using  local surrogate models to explain  the decision-  making processes  of DNN Local interpretable  model- agnostic  explanation  (LIME) Temenos et al. (2022),  Amiri et al. ( 2021),  Parmar et al. ( 2021) Attribution  visualizations and  audio Visually or audibly presenting  attribution of input variables for  a given result generated by DNN Salience maps Peng, Cui, et al. ( 2022) Graph- based  explanations Building various graph models  (including subgraphs) to link AI  results with the given input/ features Graph- based latent  representation Chang et al. ( 2020) Spectral relevance  analysis Using spectral clustering to  aggregate various local  explanations (e.g., salience maps)  towards the given results Spectral relevance  analysis Cheng et al. ( 2020) Neuron- based  explanations Decomposing gradients across  DNN layers to calculate the  contribution of hidden layer  neurons towards the given  results Neuron  conductance Wang, Gu, et al. ( 2021) Adversarial  explanations Explaining how the given AI model  could be forced to generate  wrong results Counterfactual  examples Chen et al. ( 2021)  14679671, 2023, 3, Downloaded from https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/tgis.13045, Wiley Online Library on [10/06/2026]. See the Terms and"
