      "evidence": "The paper's technical approach, which uses spectral analysis (PCA, ICA, NDVI) and spatial context (MRF), is a form of automated analysis that can lead to misclassifications when distinct real-world objects share similar spectral properties. The authors explicitly state this occurs, leading to over-detection. This aligns with the 'inadvertent inferential error' risk mechanism from Track 1.",
      "input_quote": "Because roads are spectrally similar to landslide debris (such as bare rock and exposed soil), the models sometimes misidentified municipal roads as landslides, leading to localized over-detection.",
